  "texts": [
    "We have defined two discrepancy values:• d 1: The discrepancy of the whole population.• d 2: The discrepancy of the population when excluding the individual under consideration.To assess the diversity contribution of each individual, we have devised a diversity fitness function based on the difference between d 1 and d 2.",
    "The diversity fitness function is defined as:Diversity Fitness = d 1 -d 2The rationale behind this fitness function lies in the notion that lower discrepancy values indicate better uniformity and diversity within the population.",
    "By subtracting the discrepancy of the population excluding the individual from the discrepancy of the whole population, we are essentially quantifying the impact of the individual on the overall diversity.",
    "A higher diversity fitness score suggests that the individual contributes positively to the diversity of the population, as removing it results in a higher overall discrepancy, indicating a less diverse population.",
    "This diversity fitness function serves as a metric for evaluating the contribution of each individual to the overall diversity of the population in the context of our research."
  ],
